reviews.text: A small and simple train station services by South West rail. The station could use a little TLC.

A small station located on a council estate of sort with no clear parking and only a single ticket machine which accepts cash payments. The ticket office is open in the morning on Monday to Saturday and closed all day Sunday and step free access is only accessible on the Bournemouth bound platform.

The platform for trains towards Weymouth is only accessible via a damp subway and both platforms have minimal seating and shelter. Local buses to Poole stop nearby down the road.
Not a bad little station for what it is.
Good station the line back behind platform 2 used to be the line we're the stones trains would go to the docks to take stones
Pleased never got off train very tired and run down area.
